get_power_inte...tricted_hinsts(25.10)  get_power_inte...tricted_hinsts(25.10)

Name
       get_power_intent_restricted_hinsts  -  Reports the Hinsts, which cannot
       be ungrouped or split through the create_physical_partitions command

Syntax
       get_power_intent_restricted_hinsts

       [-help]

       [-out_file <fileName>]

       Reports the Hinsts, which cannot be ungrouped or split through the cre-
       ate_physical_partitions command.  This  informs  the  user  about  such
       Hinst-level  power  intent  restrictions before using the create_physi-
       cal_partitions command and to configure UPF file for optimizing the de-
       sign.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information  for each get_power_intent_restricted_hinsts parame-
              ter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man get_power_intent_restricted_hinsts

       -out_file <fileName>
              Specifies the output <fileName> to save the UPF-restricted HInst
              information.  If  this   parameter   is   not   specified,   the
              get_power_intent_restricted_hinsts  command  displays  a list of
              Hinst names.

Related Information
       create_physical_partitions

